<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><template xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="openEHR/v1/Template" xmlns:uuid="java:java.util.UUID"><id>830b968b-be46-4a7a-9029-cc0eb2fe7ab7</id><name>Diagnostic Imaging - Nuclear Medicine - NM Meckel's Scan Order</name><description><lifecycle_state>Initial</lifecycle_state><details><purpose>For ordering a(n) NM Meckel's Scan</purpose><use/><misuse/></details><other_details><item><key>MetaDataSet:Sample Set </key><value>Template metadata sample set </value></item><item><key>Acknowledgements</key><value/></item><item><key>Business Process Level</key><value/></item><item><key>Care setting</key><value/></item><item><key>Client group</key><value/></item><item><key>Clinical Record Element</key><value/></item><item><key>Copyright</key><value/></item><item><key>Issues</key><value/></item><item><key>Owner</key><value/></item><item><key>Sign off</key><value/></item><item><key>Speciality</key><value/></item><item><key>User roles</key><value/></item></other_details></description><annotations path="[openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1]"><items><item><key>Imaging.Body Part</key><value>%=AB</value></item><item><key>Imaging.Laterality</key><value>No</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Decision Support Requirements</key><value>For all female patients of child bearing age (11-55 years) with a delayed menstrual period, possibility of pregnancy, or known pregnancy, receiving the administration of radiopharmaceuticals, consider one of the following options:a. Proceed with procedure once it has been determined that pregnancy does not exist. Order: Lab HCG.b. Provide written consent that is it in the best interest of the patient to proceed. Consent can be provided by Referring physician or Radiologist. Order: Complete consent form.c. Consider alternative imaging.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Patient Requirements</key><value>Nutrition: Hold tray, nothing to eat or drink 4 hours prior to DI exam. (South West) Water only 4 hours before exam.;Medications: (Edmonton Zone) Pre treatment with Pepcid or Zantac 30 minutes prior to exam, done in Nuclear Medicine department. (Calgary and Central Zone) 60 minutes before imaging the patient will receive 1 mg/kg (up to 50 mg) of Ranitidine in 20 ml NaCl infused over 20 minutes, done in Nuclear Medicine department.;IV requirements: Prior to coming to Nuclear Medicine department, establish peripheral IV access with saline lock attachment. (Inpatient);IV requirements: IV will be initiated in Nuclear Medicine department. (Outpatient);Imaging: Patient may be required to have an abdominal xray prior to the exam to ensure the patient has not had any recent barium. (Calgary Zone) No barium 7 days prior. (North Zone) No barium 48 hours prior.;Pediatric: Nutrition: Nothing to eat or drink as follows according to age: Less than 1 year= 2 hours, 1-12 years= 4 hours, Greater than 12 years= 6 hours.;Pediatric: Medications: Ranitidine (Zantac) dosages as per site protocol.;Pediatric: IV requirements: Prior to coming to Nuclear Medicine department, establish peripheral IV access with saline lock attachment. (Inpatient);Pediatric: IV requirements: IV will be initiated in Nuclear Medicine department. (Outpatient);</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Communication</key><value>Inpatient Clinical Communication: Females of child bearing age (11-55 years) shall complete a pregnancy screen prior to the exam. Please bring eye glasses and hearing aid if required. Notify the Nuclear Medicine department if a Translation Service is required. Breastfeeding must be completely discontinued after scan.Pediatric: Parent/legal guardian is encouraged to accompany the patient. Send translator if required.;Outpatient Clinical Communication: You must have nothing to eat or drink, except water for 4 hours before your appointment. You will receive a radioactive injection in the arm, followed by imaging. The test takes up to 1 hour to complete. Females of child bearing age (11-55 years) shall complete a pregnancy screen prior to the exam. Please bring eye glasses, hearing aid, and an interpreter if required.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Resources </key><value>http://insite.albertahealthservices.ca/assets/policy/clp-di-prov-dis2-2-1-rad-protect-female-pts.pdf</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="NM Meckel's Scan"/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B48161A11EF4549FFAE82EE73B385AF5</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017E1FD7AC82EBDEE0202A6</digest></integrity_checks></template>